        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 8. Specimen (R 45 mm) of Luidia alternata alternata (Say, 1825) (EQMN 2007): (A) abactinal and (B) actinal view of body; (C) paxillae in the abactinal plates; (D) oral region; (E) abactinal paxillae and marginal spines; (F) ambulacral furrow (proximal region on the right). Scale bars: A–B, 20 mm; C, F, 2 mm; D, 4 mm; E, 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4691100/files/figure.png" .

